\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh about two years. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well that'd be 1902 when we moved, we lived in a back - where I was born we lived in a back to back house and then - we moved to one that - wasn't a back to back you know, just an ordinary terrace house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well not far away. We moved - up Commercial Street in - from Ridge Street in - in the - in Oakworth. And we lived there about another two years and then we moved about a hundred yards further a long and lived there up to the time I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12920830 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Was that the one that you lived in longest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 That was - by the Fleece, in the village. Church Street. In Church Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You were there until you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12920830 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Do you remember why the family made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well, they were better houses. We'd - for instance in the - the back to back there would only be one bedroom you see. Then - probably just one living room with the sink in it and then we moved - because there were two bedrooms and then we moved again be
cause of the - the house we moved into then was the middle one of three. And we'd a - \{ILLEGIBLE\} and - the house was nicer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 All these houses were in Oakworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You didn't move out of Oakworth at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No. Except for - exc
ept for about eighteen months into Keighley. They were - my father's work was in Keighley and they were building rows of houses at Fell Lane and - we thought it would be nearer for me father instead of paying railway fares. But anyhow it didn't do for me 
mother's health and so - we moved back again. I can just remember - remember going to Holy Cross school as a; child. A short time, so I would be about five.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 And then you moved back into the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 We moved back into the village in Church Street. Yes. And never moved - we didn't move anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Just one sister. Who was a twin and - about two years and ten months between us and the other twin died when she was three months old.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Twenty-three I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 And engineer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What sort of engineer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Moulding. Floor moulding as they called it in those days, not the - machine moulders, distinct from a machine }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 moulder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 He worked at this job all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Yes. Except for - except for - a long strike - well, six months - about 1911 I think. You know and - and that time he filled in with the hay making jobs in the - village, just to get some money you see because there were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 strike}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  pay in those days
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Otherwise he was always a moulder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Always an engineer, yes, when - after the strike was over he went straight back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What was this other job he did while the strike was on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Just hay making. Haymaking - was summertime and - and haymaking in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So he didn't do any part time jobs or casual jobs other than this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 The only time he was out of work was during this strike period?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Twenty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oakworth. Both parents lived - both lived in Oakworth, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Had she any jobs before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12920830 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She was a weaver.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12920830 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. She did, she went back to the same mill. After we were old enough to go to school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 On marriage she finished work did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes. Until we were - we were five years old and off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she do any part time work or was it always full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Always full time, those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When you were small she didn't just go in for part time hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. I don't think - they did do part time in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She didn't start a bit later to see you off to school or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She always did the same job until she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well - she - when we were old enough of course to go to work, no, but before that she'd - she'd a very serious operation. I had to be kept - well I was of
f school to look - had to look after her and I don't think she ever went back to work. No. Then - left her an invalid. She wasn't strong enough because weaving is a - sort of job that you had to - pulls you about a bit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When your mother worked did someone look after the children or did it fit in with your school hours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well we went to - to me grandmother's for our dinners but we - we made our own - well me mother used to leave things ready for us for our breakfast and then she'd pop hom
e, they had half an hour, from eight to eight thirty and she used to see we got our breakfast and off to school and then she'd go back you see to work, and then we had our dinners at me grandmother's and then of course - she was home for - for - we used t
o go to grandmother's after school until she came home from work and then - got our tea and all at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How many rooms were there in the house at Church Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Two bedrooms, a living room and a kitchen and a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 cellar}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did anyone else besides your parents and sister live in the house, other relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No, we couldn't afford I shouldn't imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 It was done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well - of course me mother would - would mend but she never made us anything, it was me grandmother who made us things, of course she had more 
time and she - she had a sewing machine as well. We used to have things cut down - from an auntie, me mother's sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 They were second hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you get some new clothes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well - yes. But - for Sunday wear, we used - we used to have new clothes about every two years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 In Keighley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 And you used to get them about every two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What about shoes, did you get new ones or secondhand ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 We got new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did you buy the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well - mostly in Keighley I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You don't remember the shops you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 Well, they weren't such - there weren't Freeman Hardy and Willis's or anybody like that - there was - there was
 a shop in Keighley, it's now, you know, where Ramsbotham's is now, it was Uncle Chadwick's always called, half of it was a pawn shop and half of it was a - were new gods you know and that was - seemed to be one of the main shops in Keighley as I remember
. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 We used - we used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How often did you get new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Oh I should think once about every two years for shoes because we - we - me mother used to buy them big enough, in fact two sizes too big and - we used to - we had boots in winter,
 clogs for weekdays and - only shoes on Sundays if we were going visiting or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Each pair would have to do about two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, cleaning, cooking, washing-up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well he was - he was good at preparing food and - helping to wash up but - I never remember him doing any papering or decorating because me mother was good at that. Perhaps he would help but - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did he do any cleaning at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Not that I remember. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did he light the fires in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, I think he would do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Would he do any repairs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No, not much because of course it was rented property and - and - you - you relied on the landlord more or less for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 He wouldn't improve the house in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did he ever dress you or undress you or bath you when you were children, did he do things like this for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No - I don't think - I don't remember so because - it seemed to be - seemed to be always me mother who did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh yes. When -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 He took you and your sister out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No
, he took me out because of course - me sister - was delicate, being a twin and the other one dying they were - she was getting a lot of attention and - and so me father took charge of me more or less weekends and - and used to take me out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Yes, I should think he would, yes, because I remember - me father's mother lived in the village, also me mother's mother and father was going out one night and mother had said to him, have an hour ou
t for a change and - his mother saw him going past the window and turned him back and said, what was he doing going out, you know, he should be at home helping look after - so - he just have done his, he must have helped to look after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 But she didn't go out and leave him in charge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No, me sister used to scream if me father - touched her pram. She was - she was awful I remember. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Ye
s, I used to - well, we used to wash-up, my sister and me when we were older we got - we - we did a weeks turn washing up one week it was my turn, one another week. Then on Thursday nights I used to have to do the brasses, brass fender, fire irons and - r
ight and then all the cutlery because it was steel and had to be cleaned with mirror paper you know and that because I remember the fork, we had the prongs of a fork burn through me - one of me fingers once so I - got off it a bit then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How long did you continue doing these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Oh - yes, so long as we - so long as we had these brass fender and fire irons and - and - and used to do, when I got old enough, always did the ironing, I always liked ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You did that until you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your sister have any particular jobs she used to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
She was good at doing floors, we had a - we had stone stairs steps and these had to be washed down each week. My sister was good at that and washing floors. Bedroom floors and t
hings like that, doing the doorstep, she liked that and I liked the indoor jobs more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she continue to do her odd jobs until she left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes. Whiten the windows outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She did all these things after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you help your sister with things that she found difficult, like dressing or eating, when she was small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh yes. Yes. I - I can remember - being allowed to wheel her out for short - for a short - you know, going a little short way where m
e mother could see me, wheeling her pram out and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 There wouldn't be a sufficiently large difference in your ages to help her a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 great deal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No. No. She was always rather delicate and - they always seemed to be, you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 orrying about her and I sort of grew to be independent from that you see, a little bit more independent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she ever help you with anything in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh yes, we - we were good sisters together really. As far as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Can you remember anything that she did particularly to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She - she was always good at getting up in the morning. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 
When - when mother was at work you know, from six o'clock to half past eight and - and she expected us, when she came back at eight o'clock and had this
 half hour break, she expected us to be up and dressed and - then she'd make the tea or cocoa and - me sister always used to be up first though she was younger, I was always bad at getting up and she used to say, it's time to get up, it's time to get up. 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She'd be downstairs before I was. She was always good - seeing that we got up, you know, she seemed to be awake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time during your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh yes. I should think seven o'clock and - if any - any visi
tors came we were pushed off to bed straight away before that, if any visitors were expected we - I don't know why but we were always pushed off to bed. Out of sight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You weren't allowed to stay up longer for any special occasions or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well - in winter we used to get undressed and washed downstairs having no bathroom you see and - then we used to - me mother used to see we were all right and comb our hair and - and s
ee we were clean and all that and we used to trot up to bed and - I should think we had a candle and - that was it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You put yourself to bed after a while but it was your mother beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What age did you start to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Oh I - I should thing about - six years old or seven at the outside because, with mother working you see and - and father not being hoe so soon there was always work to do and - and - baking to do in those days and the washing you see in t
he evenings and so - they were glad to get us off to bed and we were out of the way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So we used to put ourselves to bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15603272\charrsid3755071  as soon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  as we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When you were about six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, onwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you share the bedroom or bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, we shared the bed and bedroom. We had a double bed in - in the - back bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What were the sleeping arrangements of the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Two bedrooms, a double bed in the front where me mother and father and a double 
bed in the back with my sister and - we had no other beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did you have your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well in front of the fire in a tin bath. We'd no hot and cold water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You always did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Until you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Once a week. Unless - for some other reason there was - we were not so well or something or - but it was a performance filling the bath with water and - in front of the fire and then we dried off and your hair washed at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 It was a certain night of the week was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Fridays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Every - every weekend. Sunday I should imagine, I remember because it was then we put our Sunday clothes on then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 In the - in the living room. The kitchen wasn't big enough for - for meals so we had them in the living room, cooked in the kitchen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room other than the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What was her cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 A gas stove. A black gas stove they were in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well at half past eight during the week we - if
 mother - when mother was working we had - our meals with my mother and - dinner with me grandmother and then had our evening meal all together. On Sundays though we had - father was at home - we had our - dinner all together Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So you usually had breakfast at about eight thirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 But your mother and father would have theirs earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So there were just the two children for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How did your mother and father manage for their breakfast, did they have it early or at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Well - father had to be up at - half past five, so had mother, so they got some - they got their breakfast then, and then me father used to take his - meal, I should think he'd take two meals something he could have - s
ay about nine o'clock and then his dinner at - dinner time. His sandwiches and - then of course we came - when he came home we had our - evening meal all together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What did you usually have for your breakfast during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well sometimes we 
had an egg, sometimes we'd treacle and bread. Never remember marmalade, it weren't in the go then I shouldn't imagine. And - sometimes we had porridge. Toast sometimes and - me mother did all her own baking, she used to make what we used to call suet cake
s which was a sort of a pastry with - made with - proper suet and - not the sort you buy in packets nowadays - and we used to have these warmed in the oven and then split open and spread with butter, they were - they were a treat. That was for breakfast.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you have anything different on certain days, perhaps on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Sundays. Yes. We perhaps had a little bit of bacon or - or sometimes I had an egg on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When did you have your midday meal, did you call it dinner or lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 We used to call it dinner at dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When did you have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Half past twelve. To one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Who was present for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 On Sundays just - just the four of us, my father, me mother and me sister and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 On Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 But during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
During the week we were - we were at me grandmother's you see until we left school and - me mother made her own dinner and - my father had his at work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You had your dinner with your grandma?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. During the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Your father took his dinner to work and your mother came home and made hers at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Some sort of thing, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When you were at your grandma's for dinner what did the usually make for you to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh we used to have me
at and potato pie on baking day and - she used to make us - a dish with onions and potatoes and - and get some potted meat from the butchers and spread it all on the top, I remember that and - brown it all off in the oven you know and - we used to have - 
c
old meat and potatoes and a vegetable on - Mondays. Tuesdays we used to have - liver and onions and dumplings baked - browned off on the top in the oven. And Wednesdays was baking day, we had meat and potato pie. Thursdays - I can't remember what we did h
a
ve on Thursdays. But Fridays was this potted meat dish. Potatoes and onions and a big dish but of course there was Uncle - Joe, Uncle Willie, Uncle Ben and me grandfather and me grandmother and then - us two, me sister and me, and then another cousin who 
she made - another cousin about our age. So - we - all in the oven, she was a good baker was me grandma. Quite a lot we used to have rice puddings 'cos everything was baked in a coal oven you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 And all these people were present for dinner every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Every - every day. At grandma's - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She made a dinner for about six of you altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 On Saturday and Sunday you had your dinner at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 We had our dinners at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Do you remember what you had, did you have anything special for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Not for Saturday we didn't. Had - I can't remember Saturdays, but Sundays of course was always a roast and Yorkshire pudding and - and a milky pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 That was on Sunday for dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 For the evening meal, would you cal it tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, during the week, yes, teatime, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Would you have that at your grandma's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, no, we all - we had that at home and me father with working in Keighley, he used to - always try and get somethi
ng to bring home like - herrings or - potted meat or - something from the pork butchers that - near where he worked and then - we used to wait until it was ready. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What time did you have your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 Oh, it'd be six o'clock - cos me father did
n't finish work until five o'clock and then he had - he had to catch a train and the railway station of course was quite the other end of Keighley you know, from Hattersley's you see, so he'd to walk all that way and then go up on the train and then walk 
up from Oakworth station you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So you used to wait for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, mother used to send me out and say, see if you can see your father coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 That was during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So you had quite a late tea during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 All together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 On Saturdays and Sundays did you have anything different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Except we had the joint for - on Sundays and of course we never had during the week, if there was any left of the joint it was used up in a stew. Wel
l - of course we had our dinners at our grandmother's but that applied the same there but - Sundays sometimes we used to have rhubarb and custard for tea or - or a jelly. But no tinned fruit. Never any tinned fruit those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Would you have the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15603272\charrsid3755071 joint}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  from dinner time if there was any left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well me father would. Not us. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You'd just have stewed fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your mother or father bake bread?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh me mother did all her own baking but me father was good as well. If - if - i
f she wasn't so well he could do that. If she - if she'd already kneaded it in - you know - kneaded the dough in the big - big baking bowl he could see to it then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she make any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she make wine or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she ever brew beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, but me grandmother did. Me grandma - remember me grandmother doing that. Of course me uncles used to be fo
nd of their own brewed beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your father and mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, we hadn't a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, we used to - there used to be allotments near us and - always - you could buy vegetables, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 lettuces}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  and - rhubarb from the garden and - during the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 during}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  the times there - you know - the summer weather and the - when the things - vegetables were ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she ever buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well we had dried peas and dried beans and dried prunes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Never anything tinned at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
No. I don't - I don't remember - the first of anything tinned coming in was tinned pineapple and tinned salmon, I can't remember anything before that. It used to be more or less rhubarb and custard and prunes and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What year would it be when you started getting tinned pineapple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Ooh I don't know, whether it would be about 1914 or before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You occasionally had a tin of fruit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. After - about 19 - I - I couldn't tell you - about 1912 or '14.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 It was before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did they keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Three or four times. Off - off t
he joint on Sundays and then afterwards - the cold meat was used up in one or two ways. So that would be about four times you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You didn't have meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Your grandma didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well she had this potted meat dish, that was - well, I expect there'd be a certain amount of meat in that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 So most days you'd have some sort of meat for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes. Yes, I - I think - we had it most days but - done up in some way. Not - not a cut off the joint, any ot
her time except Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You don't remember having tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
No. I - I don't remember ever having tinned meat. It was - well considered - like buying bread when - in my young days - buying bread you were thought to be too lazy to bake it but - nowadays things have changed haven't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Not from poaching, but they used to be on sale in Keighley, sometimes me father'd bring one and I can remember having rabbit. Stewed
 rabbit. But I never liked it because of all the small bones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 They wouldn't be poached at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15603272\charrsid3755071 no,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
 no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 He would buy it from a stall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Yes. When me father was on strike she used to - 'course he didn't have as much then either but she used to see that we - we got - what we should have. But of course we - we were all cut down. As I said before, there's no - there were no stri
ke pay and anything - I remember me grandmother used to bring us things up, make a meal for us sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your father have more than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh yes, he - he had a hard job and he - he needed it, he - he was a good - eater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. Oh no, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15603272\charrsid3755071 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, we did. We - we had to eat a bit of everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071  attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 We had to eat up unless we weren't so well. Genuinely not so well, but we had to eat up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 They would be cross if you did leave any?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 If there was something on 
the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, we could - help ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. But - that depended whether there was - was a second helping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way an sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. Me father used to say, you know, I slouched. I still slouch but me father, I always remember, he used to say - straighten that ba
ck. You know, he used to make me sit up because I sat next to me father and - me sister was near me mother and - I was within reach of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Could you bring toys or a book to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well - if
 it was - until everybody had finished unless there was some other reason that we were - going somewhere and we had to get ready for something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did you always have the same places at table?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes, we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How was the meal served, by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
By me mother - well, sometimes me father used to help, he always used to like to mash the potatoes and - do the meat of course, he carved the meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did she put everything on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes. We had no tureens. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well - the children first as they say and then - then me father and then me mother last.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Where did your younger sister sit before she could feed herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 She used to sit by me mother and - of course me mother fed her then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
Not as easy as - as father. She - she was always busy and so - me father used to - was more approachable but - I was also very fond of me grandmother. Me mother's mother. I seemed to be near - in - more 
in touch with her, she taught me to knit and sew and crochet when I was quite small. I was such a lot with my grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 You felt you could talk more easily to your grandmother than to either your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Than to any other - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your mother show any affection for you and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, she wasn't a demonstrative person. Neither was father really. Was so busy working and - getting things together I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Not really. No, I don't - I don't think so. Like I can't - I can't remember any specific incidents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Could you share them with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well I - shall we put it this way - it - I could always get anything I wanted out of me father, y
ou know, anything like but - me mother never would - you couldn't from me mother. She was never - indulge in buying us unnecessary things but me father was very good that way. And I think he - he was - I felt nearer to me father than me mother really beca
use me sister - of me sister, she was always with me mother you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 If you were worried about anything do you think you could have told your father more easily than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 I could have but I - I don't think the - the question really arose,
 we were so - lived in such a narrow circle you know, and were so provided for and - and everything you know, somehow, I don't know, I don't remember, any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh with great respect, we had to
 do as we were told and had to speak - not to say anything - we were always - not as - not as equals as they do nowadays, we were definitely subdued in that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your sister in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Yes,
 I had to - I was responsible for her and - and looked after her more or less, I was the elder sister and - and at school, we were both at the same school, I had to take her to school and bring her back and generally see that - she was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No, I never remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Well I don't know, I - I should think they - they hoped tha
t we'd get on because - they - well their family, they - there were so many of them and they all - they didn't have the opportunities that - that - there weren't many opportunities in those days either, so - I should think they just thought, you know, hop
ed we'd get on and - and be a little better than them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 Oh no, they didn't - no swearing. Didn't like that at all. I never heard my father swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15011252 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 No. No. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9522921 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 If you did something that your parents disapproved of, what would happen?
