No. Oh me father did, sorry. Me father did, he was in the church choir and he'd a very good tenor voice, and the organist - well we had a - we had a - supply organist came once and he was brother to the Lady of the Manor and she - he - t
ried to persuade me father to take lessons, you know, and take singing up really but anyhow he - he didn't, we were - we couldn't afford it I suppose and so that dropped but mother thought - me mother - when he was washing himself, when he came home from 
work he used to wash his head as well, being a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 moulder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
 you know, blustering about and he used to sing at the top of his voice and me mother used to say, shut up, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12808622\charrsid3755071 everybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10046827\charrsid3755071 
 hear you. 'Cos there was allotments behind us and all the people used to go along the path there and - dear me. He did enjoy singing.
